etymologies: mid 19th century; earliest use found in Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London. From pre- + palatal

definitions: Situated in front of or in the anterior part of the palate.

notes.text: Frequently in the context of the production of sounds in speech.

definitions: Of a sound, especially a consonant: articulated or produced with obstruction of the airstream immediately in front of the palate.
A consonant articulated with obstruction of the airstream immediately in front of the palate.
